The claim with the title 'Vos says armed citizens can defend against shooters; stats show that is rare ' says Following the feb. 14 mass shooting at Florida’s Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School that left 17 dead, Wisconsin lawmakers faced pressure on gun control. Amidst calls for tighter gun restrictions, Assembly speaker Robin Vos, R-Rochester, addressed the notion of self-defense in a february claim, stating, “ i certainly believe there are an awful lot of folks who are law-abiding who have done nothing wrong who could probably defend themselves. ”The Observatory contacted Vos and his spokesperson for comment, but they did not respond. 
